# ETF Extractor

## Overview

This project downloads ETF data from official provider websites, extracts a standard set of fields, and builds one combined CSV filtered by a whitelist of ISINs.

It is designed for repeatable daily or ad hoc runs where you want:

- raw provider exports downloaded from official sources
- provider-specific extraction logic for different file formats
- one normalized output schema across all providers
- one final combined CSV filtered by `ISIN-list.xlsx`

The examples in this README use Windows PowerShell because that matches the current repository setup, but the Python commands can be adapted to other environments.

## What The Pipeline Produces

Every processed row is normalized to the same output columns:

```text
ETF Name,Issuer,ISIN,CCY,TER(bps),AUM(M),Date
```

Field meaning:

- `ETF Name`: fund or share class name from the provider source
- `Issuer`: provider name
- `ISIN`: security identifier
- `CCY`: currency code
- `TER(bps)`: total expense ratio in basis points
- `AUM(M)`: assets under management in millions
- `Date`: date inferred from the downloaded source or snapshot

## Supported Providers

The main pipeline currently supports these providers:

| Provider key | Provider name | Raw source type | Downloader entrypoint | Extractor entrypoint |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `ishares` | iShares | `.xls` | `scrapers\ishares_extractor.py` | `providers\ishares\extract_ishares_fields.py` |
